text: Sterling is an unincorporated community in Skagit County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Sterling was laid out in 1878. A post office called Sterling was established in 1879, and remained in operation until 1890. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skagit County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Sterling, Washington
